Package: lacelang-testkit
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, libssl3
Recommends: openssl
Description: Canonical conformance test harness for Lace executors
 lace-conformance drives an executor under test through every vector in
 the Lace conformance suite (parse, validate, execute, extension types)
 and diffs the captured output against per-vector expected results.
 .
 This package contains a self-contained binary with every vector
 embedded at build time. The executor under test is any language
 implementation of the Lace probe scripting language, invoked via `-c
 <cmd>` or `-m <manifest.toml>`.
 .
 TLS scenarios use the bundled HTTPS mock server (OpenSSL-linked). The
 per-scenario test certs are generated at install time via the openssl
 CLI. If openssl is not installed, certs are skipped with a clear warning
 and HTTPS-requiring vectors are reported as skipped; run
 `lace-conformance --generate-certs` after installing openssl to populate
 them manually.
